reviews.review_text: Hard to find better Thanx Bob, Louis, and Derek.  A rich, warm, clear audience recording, in fact 5 stars just for that.  I don't need to hear the board.  Energetic and adventurous playing from start to finish.  Bob tunes are very rocking.  Crazy Fingers is a true gem The most elegaic Peggy-O ever.  Slipknot is very spacey.  I love Keith on the electric piano.  Amazing touches by him.  Some of the other copies of this show have reviews mentioning stage banter.  There is none present here except the intro and outro.  This is a must!  Peace

Download me now or you are an idiot This is an amazing recording, tweak a little with the EQ, Jerry rifs are crisp, flowy, goodness. From the opening song, you know it is going to be a special night, crowd into it, mana from heaven, thank you archive.

So fun 75...fly on, baby..yeah..fly on. 

 Super jazzy Help/Slip/Frank. Love it.
